elements.title: 3C 345
elements.contents: ... that the quasar 3C 345 has a jet (pictured) that appears to move five to fifteen times faster than the speed of light?

elements.title: Patricia Davies
elements.contents: ... that Patricia Davies and Jean Argles, two sisters who signed the Official Secrets Act as World War II codebreakers, did not find out about each other's top-secret work until the 1960s?

elements.title: Keine Kameraden
elements.contents: ... that in 1978, Keine Kameraden's findings – that 3.3 million Soviet prisoners of war died of ideologically motivated mistreatment – caused a sensation in Germany?

elements.title: Luisa González
elements.contents: ... that 2023 Ecuadorian presidential candidate Luisa González was pepper-sprayed by the National Police while on her way to register her candidacy?

elements.title: Preußisches Obertribunal
elements.contents: ... that few decisions have instigated more discussion in German criminal law scholarship than an 1859 judgement of the Preußisches Obertribunal?

elements.title: A Little Sound
elements.contents: ... that A Little Sound began uploading music to her YouTube channel when she was eleven years old?

elements.title: Noel Road
elements.contents: ... that Kenneth Halliwell murdered his lover Joe Orton with a hammer at their flat in London's Noel Road, before taking a drug overdose?

elements.title: Ben Phillips
elements.contents: ... that Ben Phillips replaced his friend's hair gel with superglue, put Viagra in his sports drink, and placed him on a lake while he slept on an inflatable mattress?
